OL,6,FHe said: "Who do we support this week?
OL,7,FWho can we not support this week? Can
OL,8,Fwe reduce the size of the parcels so
OL,9,Feveryone gets something? Horrible
OL,10,Fdecisions have to be made and it's not
OL,11,Fsomething that we want to do or enjoy
OL,12,Fdoing.
OL,14,F"It's often staff who are on minimum
OL,15,Fwage. They're in tourism, retail, and
OL,16,Fhospitality. And by week three of the
OL,17,Fmonth, they're struggling to make ends
OL,18,Fmeet. Some of our clients work a
OL,19,Fcouple of jobs. And by that point in
OL,20,Fthe month, they're running out of
OL,21,Ffunds to put food on the table."
